stylometry: @RISK enables us to get a fair comparison quickly and easily by running several simulations at once. We can have several different inputs and receive the results of each. When we run a simulation with 5 inputs, @RISK will run a simulation for each of those inputs how ever many iterations we ask it to. It will then show results of each input, showing the MIN, MEAN, MAX, and ST DEV of the output (such as profit) that we are wanting to track. The best solution of the results is typically the one with the highest MEAN(or lowest mean depending on what you are tracking, highest mean being related to something such as profit, and lowest meand being related to something such as cost), related to the the lowest ST DEV.
